@Node "Introduction"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}

DoubleDrawerBall is a directory tool, allowing you listing drawer(s) and/or file(s) in two windows and process functions on
them independently.
DoubleDrawerBall is started from @{"Ambient" link "wb"} or @{"Shell" link "use"} with one option required; directory.
By startup is the directory listed. At top is amount of drawer(s), file(s) and total bytes filesizes (64bits) given.
Shows for filesystem SFS filesize up to 4Gb. 64bits filesizes possible with 64bit filesystem.
@EndNode
@Node "Distribution" 
@{b}Distribution and copyright@{ub}

DoubleDrawerBall is freeware.
@EndNode
@Node "Tip" 
@{b}Tip@{ub}

*recommended is SFS as filesystem, because it supports long filenames more seen nowadays. SFSDoctor 1.5 in MorphOS 2 distribution
 helps me once to recover 240 files by a crash. Do not anoying validating whole harddisk so now and then as FFS does.
 HDConfig in MorphOS 2.5 is bugfixed.

*you can copy text from any other programm in the rename string gadget: click left mouse-button and move with the mouse over the
 text you wanna copy, release then the left mouse-button, and press the right special "Amiga" (Windows) key with key "C". Go to
 DoubleDrawerBall and press special right "Amiga" (Windows) key with key "V" in the rename window string gadget. Other handy text
 controls: press key "Shift" and "left arrow" key to go to the beginning of the textline, "Shift" and "right arrow" key to the
 end of the textline. "Shift"+"Del" delete all text right of the cursor.
@EndNode
