@Node "use" "How to use DoubleDrawerBall"

DoubleDrawerBall is started from Shell.

@{u}@{b}Shell usage:@{uu}@{ub}

The following commandline options are supported:
------------------------------------------------

TEMPLATE:

	DoubleDrawerBall,NAME

NAME=directory or device to show at startup, use no quotes, name with spaces are readed OK.


Shell (CLI) Examples:
---------------------

@{fg shine}-1-@{fg text}

@{fg fill}DoubleDrawerBall DH0:@{fg text}

List the device DH0: in a window lister

@{fg shine}-2-@{fg text}

@{fg fill}DoubleDrawerBall Work:MorphOS/Butter fly@{fg text}

List the directory "Work:MorphOS/Butter fly" in a window lister
@EndNode
@Node "wb" "Ambient"
@{b}Starting from Ambient@{ub}

DoubleDrawerBall can be started from Ambient from the icon, SYS: as directory is loaded by default in the left lister,
RAM: in the right lister.
You can select file(s) and/or drawer(s) in the two windows and choose a function from the @{"pull-down menus" link "pulldownmenus"}
to process on them after each other. Additionaly, you can create own defined @{"user menus" link "pdm_project_settings_usermenus"}.
@EndNode
@Node "Require" "Requirements"

Minimal Requirements:

MorphOS 2+ and 24bit screen(s)
@EndNode
@Node "bugs" "Known bugs"

-1 Pulldown-menu "File/Information" don't work with RAM: T:, nothing happens. Also it's shown on Ambient screen.
   Do not works when name contain spaces.
-2 Removable media as USB connected drives, memorysticks and CD-ROM gives the follow troubles:
   Hangs the lister by refreshing, because the transfer is not finished yet, clicking arround at gadgets and so on
   helps mostly. Advice is to copy/delete file(s), not whole drawer(s), so it's not confused.
   Problems with USB: copy drawers USB memorystick endlessly copy same file, can't get out of the subdir.
   copy bootpartition from my Pegasos II to USB memorystick goes OK.
   copy single files from USB memorystick goes OK.
   Update 0.9m+MOS 2.4 copy drawers on CD-ROM to other media, only one file in each (sub)dir is copied. Copy drawers from
   USB memorystick to other media: gives copycheck requester asking overwrite file (these copied before), choose
   "Skip all" and all files in each (sub)dir is copied correctly. Seems for me the unbuffered Read() Write() causes the
   troubles. Copy delay helps not. The special DoubleDrawerBall version which use asyncio library helps not either.
   DoubleDrawerBall do not check if disk is ejected.
   Solution is to use the standard MorphOS copy in an usermenu.
-3 Can crash on fonts which some characters are lower then the heigth, you see this when some height character becomes
   partialy selected, as of by font "Euler" does. Font "Bitstream Vera Sans" only in size 21, other sizes OK.
-4 When a directory failed to be loaded, the window has no title, do not process a function, it crashes then,
   do open new directory or choose from history
-5 When (more times) pressed OK button in buffer settings window, it can happen that the windowtitle is named "SYS:", altough
   another directory is loaded. Strange enough, clicking outside the window, and the correct title appears, window is
   then deactivated. Activate the window again, and it's named SYS: Seems SetWindowTitles() causes this by own screen,
   because DrawerBall(BMBGRA) do not have this behaviour. Therefor, i do not use it in DoubleDrawerBall, only in the 
   buffer settings window, i must pass a new title address then. A solution might be closing then opening the window.
   Save settings then starting DoubleDrawerBall is OK.
-6 years 2100 and above are wrong displayed date, as of by audio-CD with shows randomly date.
   Solution is to set date correctly or load from internet with command SetClockNTP.
@EndNode
@Node "tech" "Technical"

*DoubleDrawerBall uses an off-screen ARGB regtangle allocated once by startup.

*DoubleDrawerBall.img is the background image resides in the DoubleDrawerBall directory.

*DoubleDrawerBall.guide resides in the same directory DoubleDrawerBall is, to let pull-down menu
 "Project/Help" working, this is checked, nothing happens when it's not present.

*For MorphOS 2.x users: the screen opened is a 2D layer screen. Advantage is that you can scrolling with "AWeb II" without crashing.
@EndNode
@Node "Compilation" "Compilation of DoubleDrawerBall"
    
DoubleDrawerBall is assembled with vasm & vlink from the vbcc C package.

Freeware software used:

MCalc -programmers suitable calculator. (MOS)
Snoopium -shows much system calls, good for anylizing programs. (MOS)
Scout -shows much information about the Pegasos, also screens/windows (MOS)
AutoDocReader -to read autodocs that bescribes the Amiga/MorphOS functions. (MOS)
PPC680x0 -translate 68K sources to PPC, without it, this program was not possible.
CygnusEd Professional V4.23 PPC -famous texteditor. (MOS)
Blender 3D 2.46, painted icon with. (MOS)

My Amiga configuration:

 Amiga1200T 68060 59Mhz, 603e 200Mhz, ROM 3.1, OS3.9 BB2, RAM 128Mb, SCSI HD 8Gb,
 IDE DVD 16x40x, SCSI CD-R 6x4x, PARALLELZIP 100Mb, FlickerFixer/Scandoubler,
 Mediator Voodoo5 graphics with picasso96

 Processor board is BlizzardPPC with SCSI2 (Overclocked the 68060 to 59Mhz)

My Pegasos II configuration:

 Pegasos II G4 1Ghz, MorphOS 1.4.5, 3.6, 1GbRAM, PHILIPS DVDR16LS Dual DVD with LIGHTSCRIBE,
 WD 120G HD, Transcend 32G 600X CF, Belinea 107065 monitor, PixelView Pro TV-Radio, Bang&Olufsen Beosound8 speakerset,
 Radeon 9250, Elbox USB2 card (it's almost empty, they show an older model on their website www.elbox.com).
 Efika, Mac mini 1.5Ghz, Mac G5 2,7Ghz
@EndNode
