@Node "pdm_project_settings_listerc" "Pull-down menu Setings/Lister colors"
@{b}Pull-down menu Setings/Lister colors@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the window lister gradient colors, file color
and drawer color. For each are three @{b}R@{ub}ed, @{b}G@{ub}reen and @{b}B@{ub}lue sliders present.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_project_settings_windowc" "Pull-down menu Setings/Windows colors"
@{b}Pull-down menu Setings/Windows colors@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the windows gradient colors, text color.
For each are three @{b}R@{ub}ed, @{b}G@{ub}reen and @{b}B@{ub}lue sliders present.
These colors are used for opened windows as for example the "Rename" window.
Note, that on resize the window the position and width is then used for all opened windows.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_project_settings_buffersizes" "Pull-down menu Setings/Buffer sizes"
@{b}Pull-down menu Setings/Buffer sizes@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the follow buffers in megabytes:
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Copy:@{fg text}@{bg back}      the buffer used for copy, if set to 10, means 10Mb is used, a 20Mb file is then copied in 2 parts.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Lister:@{fg text}@{bg back}    buffer holding filenames, do not use large values here
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Dir stack:@{fg text}@{bg back} do not use large values here
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Dir depth:@{fg text}@{bg back} buffer holding fileinfoblocks, do not use large values here, actualy, 1 is enough for 984 subdirectories tree deep
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Bitmap:@{fg text}@{bg back}    buffer for the off-screen ARGB regtangle used for display, great values are used here,
            my download directory needs 80Mb !
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_project_settings_dateformats" "Pull-down menu Setings/Date formats"
@{b}Pull-down menu Setings/Date formats@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the Date format.
Takes effect on the right window after processing a function.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_project_settings_usermenus" "Pull-down menu Setings/User menus"
@{b}Pull-down menu Setings/User menus@{ub}

An "User menus settings" window is opened where you can change the usermenus or add them if not present.
Click on an already created usermenu button and an usermenu titled window opens,
here you can change the usermenu items or add them if not present.
Click on an already created usermenu items button and an "Usermenuitem function settings" window
opens. In the first two strings, you can change the usermenu name and menuitem name.
Remember, an usermenu(s) is not created if it has no menuitem(s).

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} define the commandline programm executing

 an usermenu execute requires that are at least one file or drawer is selected.
 supported options are case sensetive and always begins with percentage character: 

 @{"%P" link "oP"} path source drawer lister with slash, example -> DH1:Graphics/mypictures/
 @{"%p" link "o_p"} path source drawer lister without slash, example -> DH1:Graphics/mypictures
 @{"%s" link "o_s"} source (selected) file or drawer
 @{"%S" link "oS"} source (selected) file or drawer without extension, example -> Symphony.melody.mp3 becomes Symphony.melody
 @{"%D" link "oD"} destination drawer with slash, example -> Downloads:mypictures/
 @{"%d" link "o_d"} destination drawer without slash, example -> Downloads:mypictures
 @{"%i" link "o_i"} input window, usage: %i<MYWINDOWTEXT>%i where <MYWINDOWTEXT> is the text that appears in the input window.
 @{"%h" link "o_h"} comment text, which contains often the http:// string if file was downloaded from the internet
 @{"%c" link "o_c"} currentdir destination directory, can be placed anywhere in the commandline once.
 @{"%C" link "oC"} currentdir own defined directory, can be placed anywhere in the commandline once, usage: %C<MYCURRENTDIR>%C
 @{"%n" link "o_n"} next function commandline behind this option.
 @{"%r" link "o_r"} refresh source lister.
 @{"%R" link "oR"} refresh destination lister.
 @{"%l" link "o_l"} lister refreshed with new defined drawer, enable "Start always" too. Do not use other options together with this option %l

 @{i}notes about the options:@{ui}

 to read selected file(s) and/or drawer(s) that contain spaces in their name(s), use quotionmarks arround the option(s):
 "%s" only not when "All atonce" is enabled, then %s
 "%P%s" source path+filename
 "%D%s" destination path+filename

 if pressed "Cancel" in the input window, the executing for this selection is aborted, goes on with next then.

 option %c or %C only once used on a commandline, do not use both the same time in a commandline

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Output window:@{fg text}@{bg back} output properties, at end is the enable button.

 own output window enabled: once opened and all outputs from all selections goes to if "Multitasking" is not enabled.
 is "Multitasking" enabled, then for each selection is an output window opened !
 output window is closed if an usermenu executing happens again, last one is closed by quiting DoubleDrawerBall,
 this is not by "Multitasking" enabled, then it must wait when the executed command is finished.

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Stack in Kb:@{fg text}@{bg back} stack is measured in Kbytes, in the Ambient Information window, it's in bytes.
 Thus first divide with 1024 to be DoubleDrawerBall compatible.

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Priority:@{fg text}@{bg back} give priority, default zero.

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Multitasking:@{fg text}@{bg back} enable multitasking, default disabled.
 some programms multitasks always, even if DoubleDrawerBall "Multitasking" button is not enabled.

@{fg shine}@{bg text}All atonce:@{fg text}@{bg back} if "All atonce" is enabled, option %s holds all selections and the commandline is executed once.
 keep in mind that the commandline is limited in lenght, so you can not choose to much selected files/drawers then !
 Works not with option %S, adviced is to not used this function when it is not realy needed.

@{fg shine}@{bg text}Start always:@{fg text}@{bg back} execute usermenu once regardles of selected file(s) and/or drawer(s).
 for launching a single programm needed. function do not deselect bar(s) when finished
@EndNode
@Node "oP" "Example %P"
@{u}Example %P@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} Workbench:Multimedia/PointRider "@{b}%P@{ub}%s"

Try first if a command works with "%s" only, PointRider fails that so use than "%P%s"
@EndNode
@Node "o_p" "Example %p"
@{u}Example %p@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} Workbench:Tools/SearchStar_MOS "@{b}%p@{ub}" "%iEnter file name to search for%i" RAM:

SearchStar_MOS is a programm that searches for files in the directory given by %p
@{fg shine}@{bg text}Start always@{fg text}@{bg back} button is enabled, so SearchStar_MOS starts without file(s) and/or drawer(s) selected.
@EndNode
@Node "o_s" "Example %s"
@{u}Example %s@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} Workbench:Graphics/SimpleView "@{b}%s@{ub}"

SimpleView is an image viewer, that shows the image given by %s
@EndNode
@Node "oS" "Example %S"
@{u}Example %S@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} C:lame -h "%s" "%D@{b}%S@{ub}.mp3"%R

lame convert .wav music to .mp3 music files, given by %S
@EndNode
@Node "oD" "Example %D"
@{u}Example %D@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} C:Copy "%s" TO "@{b}%D@{ub}%s" ALL CLONE%R

standard MorphOS copy command used to copy files and/or drawers to the full path destination directory given by %D
@EndNode
@Node "o_d" "Example %d"
@{u}Example %d@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} C:unlzx -x "%s" -o "@{b}%d@{ub}"%R

Extract .lzx archives to the destination directory given by %d
@EndNode
@Node "o_i" "Example %i"
@{u}Example %i@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} C:lha a -x -r "%D@{b}%i@{ub}Enter LHA archive name, at end is .lha appended@{b}%i@{ub}" %s%R

Build .lha archive from (more) files and/or drawers with the name given in the input window

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}All atonce@{fg text}@{bg back} button enabled for archives.
@EndNode
@Node "o_h" "Example %h"
@{u}Example %h@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} Workbench:Internet/AWeb/AWeb "@{b}%h@{ub}"

Load the internet location (again) in the webbrowser AWeb what's often stored in the comment text by internet programms.
@EndNode
@Node "o_c" "Example %c"
@{u}Example %c@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} @{b}%c@{ub}C:lha e "%P%s"%R

Extract .lha archives, writed in the destination directory by the command lha.
@EndNode
@Node "oC" "Example %C"
@{u}Example %C@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} TiMidity -oahiplay "%P%s"@{b}%C@{ub}Workbench:Music/TiMidity@{b}%C@{ub}

Timidity, an AmigaOS4 programm running under the OS4 emulator in MorphOS, plays midi songs. It needs to look up for files,
samples in the directory given by option %C.
@EndNode
@Node "o_n" "Example %n"
@{u}Example %n@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} vbcc:bin/vasmppc_std -opt-branch -Felf -o T:a.o "%s"@{b}%n@{ub}vbcc:bin/vlink -belf32amiga -s -x -P__abox__ -P__amigappc__ -o RAM:aout T:a.o@{b}%n@{ub}echo "assembled..."

Three programms are executed after each other; vasmppc_std, vlink and echo.
@EndNode
@Node "o_r" "Example %r"
@{u}Example %r@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} C:jhead -purejpg -di -dx "%s"@{b}%r@{ub}

Refresh the lister to see the (writed) optimized .jpg pictures by the programm jhead.
@EndNode
@Node "oR" "Example %R"
@{u}Example %R@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} C:mpg123 -w "%D%S.wav" "%P%s"@{b}%R@{ub}

mpg123 convert .mp3 sounds to .wav sounds, visible (writed) in the destination lister refreshed by option %R.
@EndNode
@Node "o_l" "Example %l"
@{u}Example %l@{uu}

 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Function:@{fg text}@{bg back} @{b}%l@{ub}Workbench:Downloads

Load the directory Workbench:Downloads in this lister
@{fg shine}@{bg text}Start always@{fg text}@{bg back} button must be enabled.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_project_settings_listerview" "Pull-down menu Setings/Lister view"
@{b}Pull-down menu Setings/Lister view@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the lister view appearances.
Takes effect on the right window after processing a function.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Extra space filename:@{fg text}@{bg back} By default is 1, set zero if you want the most compact width window, beware then
                       it can happen that by non-proportional fonts the longest filename directly to the
                       largest filesize is, without space.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Stay selected:@{fg text}@{bg back}        Selected file(s) and/or drawer(s) stay(s) selected after process a function.
                       Default not enabled.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Protect and comment:@{fg text}@{bg back}  By default protection and comment are listed.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Max. height:@{fg text}@{bg back}          Height boundery for window can be modified, zero means screen dimensions used,
                       checked min. height is 256.
                       Be sure that height is not greater then screenheight.
                       DoubleDrawerBall takes care for the window borders, tough.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Screen width, height: (restart)@{fg text}@{bg back} Screen width and height can be modified, zero means Ambient screen sizes used,
                       you must save settings first then restart the programm to use the new screen sizes.
                       Be sure that width and height for the 24bit screen is correct.
                       Always the actual screen width and height is shown.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}No cgx_wpa:@{fg text}@{bg back}           Disable CGX/WritePixelArray() for display and scrolling only, used is then my own
                       programmed custom writepixelarray routine.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Mouse reaction:@{fg text}@{bg back}       Time delay when mouse is ready, zero is fastest but can selecting to early (1/50 sec.)
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_project_settings_copyrename" "Pull-down menu Setings/Copy, rename"
@{b}Pull-down menu Setings/Copy, rename@{ub}

A settings window is opened where you can change the copy, rename settings.
Takes effect on the right window after processing a function.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Copy comment:@{fg text}@{bg back}  by default enabled, faster copy when disabled.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Unprotects:@{fg text}@{bg back}    overwrite protected files by copy.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Overwrite check:@{fg text}@{bg back} see if file becomes overwrited by copy, faster copy if not enabled.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Rename text:@{fg text}@{bg back}   toggle "name", then the rename window stringinput holds the name (default), "Stays" first name
                and previous input(s) stays, handy for multiple renames with different versions of the same name.
                "Empty", then rename window stringinput is clear, handy to copy&paste text(s) in.
 @{fg shine}@{bg text}Copy delay 1/50s@{fg text}@{bg back} Add delay in 1/50 seconds after file is entirely copied, default 75=1.5 sec. PFS-II filesystem
                needs it.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_project_savesettings" "Pull-down menu Project/Save settings"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/Save settings@{ub}

Save settings for this active lister. The left lister has the global settings, the right lister can
only saved the gradient colors and buffer settings.
Each lister has own user-menus settings stored in an own settingsfile.
Sort mode is also saved.
Position and width opened windows are saved too.
Stored in the directory DoubleDrawerBall is in.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_project_help" "Pull-down menu Project/Help"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/Help@{ub}

Launch the amigaguide documentation
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_project_about" "Pull-down menu Project/About"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/About@{ub}

Programm version and assembling date information.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_project_quit" "Pull-down menu Project/Quit"
@{b}Pull-down menu Project/Quit@{ub}

Quit programm quickly.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_file_openwith" "Pull-down menu File/Open with"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Open with@{ub}

A requester appears, choose a programm to execute with the selected file(s) and/or drawer(s).
Selections are processed after each other.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_file_copy" "Pull-down menu File/Copy"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Copy@{ub}

Copies selected file(s) and/or drawer(s) from the active to the inactive lister.
If a file will becoming overwrited, a window appears for asking skipping or replacing this file.
Also you can choose "Skip all", "Replace all" and "Abort" copy. "Version" button allows you to compare
the version of the overwritten file,
@{"copy buffer" link "pdm_project_settings_buffersizes"} is used to load the file and search the version. Is the file bigger in size, increase
then the copy buffer because the last part of the file isn't searched in.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_file_delete" "Pull-down menu File/Delete"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Delete@{ub}

Requester appears asking if you are sure deleting file(s) and/or drawer(s).
Pressing "OK" button deletes the selected file(s) and/or drawer(s).
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_file_newdrawer" "Pull-down menu File/New drawer"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/New drawer@{ub}

Create new drawer, also drawer icon can be created. If drawer already exists, an icon can be created too for this drawer.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_file_rename" "Pull-down menu File/Rename"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Rename@{ub}

Rename selected file(s) and/or drawer(s). Press close gadget to abort.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_file_info" "Pull-down menu File/Information"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Information@{ub}

Gives the Information window for the selected file(s) and/or drawer(s).
It appears 10 times if 10 selected files were chosen, it's an own task.
In the information window, you can modify comment and protection bits, version for files can be shown
as well as total filesize in drawers.
Refresh lister by yourself, because DoubleDrawerBall can not determine if information requester returns
and save or cancel button was pressed.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_file_version" "Pull-down menu File/Version"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Version@{ub}

Gives the version for the selected file(s), libraries.
@{"copy buffer" link "pdm_project_settings_buffersizes"} is used to load the file and search the version. Is the file bigger in size, increase
then the copy buffer because the last part of the file isn't searched in.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_file_search" "Pull-down menu File/Search"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Search@{ub}

Search in this window a name, the matched file(s) and/or drawer(s) becomes selected. Already selected
are ignored. Disable the "Ignore case" button for case sensetive searching.
Enable the "Thru files" button for searching into files, in (sub)dirs is not searched thru files.
@{"copy buffer" link "pdm_project_settings_buffersizes"} is used to search thru the file. Is the file bigger in size, increase
then the copy buffer because the last part of the file isn't searched in.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_file_execute" "Pull-down menu File/Execute"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Execute@{ub}

Execute the selected file(s) and/or drawer(s) with the commandline arguments typed in the execute window.
"file is not executable" requester appears if file can not be executed.
Press close gadget to abort.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_file_selall" "Pull-down menu File/Select all"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Select all@{ub}

Select all file(s) and/or drawer(s).
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_file_invall" "Pull-down menu File/Invert all"
@{b}Pull-down menu File/Invert all@{ub}

Toggles file(s) and/or drawer(s) selections inverted.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_sort_nosort" "Pull-down menu Sort/No sort"
@{b}Pull-down menu Sort/No sort@{ub}

Listed the drawer(s) and file(s) as it appears on disk.
Handy in some cases.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_sort_namecase" "Pull-down menu Sort/Name case"
@{b}Pull-down menu Sort/Name case@{ub}

Listed the drawer(s) and/or file(s) alphabeticaly, uppercases at top.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_sort_date" "Pull-down menu Sort/Date"
@{b}Pull-down menu Sort/Name Date@{ub}

Listed the drawer(s) and/or file(s) at newest date.
Most recent date at top.
@EndNode
@Node "pdm_history" "Pull-down menu History"
@{b}Pull-down menu History@{ub}

Listed are the visited directories, oldest at top. At startup are the volumes/assigns listed.
@EndNode
